Question_1.Context: The paper discusses the synthesis and characterization of new heterometallic gold metallacages. The compounds were characterized using various techniques.
Question_1.Question: What method was used to determine the elemental composition of the synthesized compounds?
Question_1.Source: Elemental analyses of carbon, hydrogen, nitrogen, and sulfur were determined using a Heraeus vario EL elemental analyzer.

Question_2.Context: The paper discusses the cytotoxicity of the synthesized metallacages on different cancer cell lines.
Question_2.Question: Which compound showed the highest cytotoxicity against the PC-3 prostate cancer cell line?
Question_2.Source: The IC50 values [µM] for the selected metallacages and their uncoordinated ligands were determined. [Lu{Au(Ldiethyl)}3] showed the lowest IC50 value of 2.3 ± 1.9 µM on the PC-3 cell line.

Question_3.Context: The paper describes the radiolabeling experiments with 68Ga for the synthesized compounds.
Question_3.Question: What was the radiochemical purity of [68Ga][Ga{Au(Ldiethyl)}2]+ after radiolabeling?
Question_3.Source: The radiochemical purity of [68Ga][Ga{Au(Ldiethyl)}2]+ was 82% as measured by radio-HPLC.

Question_4.Context: The paper discusses the stability of the radiolabeled complexes in human serum.
Question_4.Question: What was the stability assessment outcome for [68Ga][Ga{Au(Lmorph)}2]+ with human serum albumin?
Question_4.Source: The complexes [68Ga][Ga{Au(Lmorph)}2]+ and [68Ga][Ga{Au(Ldiethyl)}2]+ were not stable under the tested conditions, with approximately 80% of free 68Ga appearing in the iTLC-chromatogram with citrate buffer as the mobile phase.

Question_5.Context: The paper discusses the radiolabeling experiments with 198Au for the synthesized compounds.
Question_5.Question: What was the radiochemical purity of [198Au][Ga{Au(Ldiethyl)}2]+ after radiolabeling?
Question_5.Source: The complex [198Au][Ga{Au(Ldiethyl)}2]+ was received in a total of 71.2% radiochemical purity.

Question_6.Context: The paper discusses the synthesis and characterization of new heterometallic gold metallacages.
Question_6.Question: What technique was used to determine the crystal structures of the synthesized complexes?
Question_6.Source: The crystal structures of the complexes were determined by single-crystal X-ray diffraction.

Question_7.Context: The paper discusses the cytotoxicity of the synthesized metallacages on different cancer cell lines.
Question_7.Question: Which compound showed the highest cytotoxicity against the U343 human glioblastoma cell line?
Question_7.Source: The IC50 values [µM] for the selected metallacages and their uncoordinated ligands were determined. [Lu{Au(Ldiethyl)}3] showed the lowest IC50 value of 0.8 ± 0.6 µM on the U343 cell line.

Question_8.Context: The paper describes the radiolabeling experiments with 177Lu for the synthesized compounds.
Question_8.Question: What was the radiochemical purity of [177Lu][Lu{Au(Ldiethyl)}3] after radiolabeling?
Question_8.Source: The radio-chromatogram of [177Lu][Lu{Au(Ldiethyl)}3] showed a peak at tR = 18.2 min, representing the complex in 17% radiochemical purity.

Question_9.Context: The paper discusses the stability of the radiolabeled complexes in human serum.
Question_9.Question: What was the stability assessment outcome for [177Lu][Lu{Au(Lmorph)}3] with human serum albumin?
Question_9.Source: The complex [177Lu][Lu{Au(Lmorph)}3] was not stable under the tested conditions, with free 177Lu appearing in the iTLC-chromatogram.

Question_10.Context: The paper discusses the synthesis and characterization of new heterometallic gold metallacages.
Question_10.Question: What technique was used to determine the mass spectra of the synthesized compounds?
Question_10.Source: The mass spectra were measured with an Agilent 6210 ESI-TOF spectrometer.
